==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} *{{term||overheren|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term/t|ang|oferhīeran||to overhear, hear, disobey, disregard, neglect}}, equivalent to {{prefix|over|hear}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|overhoren||to hear, hear about|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|überhören||to not hear, ignore|lang=de}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|overhøre||to overhear|lang=da}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|yfirheyra||to hear|lang=is}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/oʊ.vɚ.hɪɚ/}}
* {{rhymes|ɪə(ɹ)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|overhears|overhearing|overheard}}

# To [[hear]] something that wasn't meant for one's ears.

